record_exploration_finding
{
  "path": "crates/nyctos-api/src/router.rs",
  "line": 141,
  "cap": "CRED_EXPOSURE",
  "endpoint": "all auth-gated /api/v1/* (token in ?token=)",
  "rationale": "check_query_token accepts the bearer in the URL query string (router.rs:141-152). TraceLayer::new_for_http() (router.rs:89) writes the request URI to tracing output by default, so every authenticated request logs the bearer in cleartext to whatever subscriber the operator wired (stderr, file, journald, etc). URL-query tokens also leak via browser history, Referer on navigation, and any reverse-proxy access log placed in front of the daemon. The constant-time comparison at :154 is defeated upstream because the secret already crossed three logging surfaces. Static pass missed because the bug is a misuse pattern (logging-by-default of a transport-level secret), not a missing escape.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "grep daemon stderr / journald output for 'token=' after any authenticated GET; confirm the bearer is recoverable from logs."
}

